This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on neural machine translation. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel domain adaptation method for NMT, which is a common research area in cs.CL. 

The paper also involves the use of artificial tags to indicate specific domains, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

As the paper involves training and fine-tuning neural networks, it may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

The proposed method involves combining two existing approaches, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, as the paper involves working with parallel corpora, it may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision), which often involves working with image and text data.
